Dear Ajit,

I am assuming your e-mail indicates that you believe Shivratri should be celebrated on March 5 (at least on the east coast). Now I just got off the phone with our temple priest and his logic is that we should use the tithi at sunrise because that is the time when we take the sankalpa for the fast! I have always felt that using the tithi prevailing at sunrise for the rest of the day till the next sunrise for our festivals must be due to some good reasons but no one has explained that me as yet!

Clearly, this is something that we (as Hindus) need to resolve. But, I guess, unanimity on just about anything has never been one of the characteristics of our tradition...

regards,
Chandraprakash

